HEADWORD: Turks-head
<hw>Turk's"-head`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>A knot of turbanlike form worked on a rope with a piece of small
line.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The melon cactus.</def> <mark>[West
Indies]</mark> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Any of several species of
<gen>Echinocactus</gen>.</def> <mark>[California]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A long-handled, round-headed broom for sweeping
ceilings, etc.</def> <mark>[Colloq. or Dial.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Turlupin</ent>⟦br⟧
